data = hdu[0].data
xx = header['CRVAL1'] + header['CDELT1'] * (np.arange(header['NAXIS1']) - header['CRPIX1'])
yy = header['CRVAL2'] + header['CDELT2'] * (np.arange(header['NAXIS2']) - header['CRPIX2'])

plt.imshow(data[0,-1,:,:], origin='lower', aspect='auto', extent=(xx[0], xx[-1], yy[0], yy[-1]))
plt.colorbar(label=r'$T_B$ (K)')

In[6]:
# clip a spectrum for x = -1000 arcsec y= -100 arcsec

x_pix = int(np.argmin(np.abs(xx - (-1000))))
y_pix = int(np.argmin(np.abs(yy - (-100))))

print(x_pix, y_pix)

spectrum = data[0, :, y_pix, x_pix]

freqs = hdu[1].data['cfreqs']

plt.plot(freqs/1e6, spectrum)
plt.xlabel('Frequency (MHz)')
plt.ylabel('T_B (K)')
plt.title(f'Spectrum at x={xx[x_pix]} y={yy[y_pix]}')
plt.yscale('log')
